Scala example is wrong, wouldn&#x27;t even compile; should be:<p><pre><code>    def blubExtra(a: Int, b: Int): Int = blub(inc(a), inc(b))
</code></pre>
The original would need an equals thrown in there, otherwise it&#x27;s procedural syntax (IIRC, has been deprecated or will be in the next release) which has a return type of Unit, thus not compiling when specifying a return type of Int.<p><pre><code>    def blubExtra(a: Int, b: Int): Int = {
      blub(inc(a), inc(b))
    }</code></pre>
